humanMachineDialogue.author: Memory Reasoning
humanMachineDialogue.text: According to the report, sentinel lymph node #1 (SLN #1) has metastatic carcinoma, while sentinel lymph node #2 (SLN #2) is negative for metastases. In the right axillary contents levels 1 and 2, metastatic carcinoma is found in 4 out of 24 lymph nodes. Based on the new rules provided, N1 indicates metastases in 1 to 3 axillary lymph nodes. Since metastases are found in 1 out of 2 sentinel lymph nodes and 4 out of 24 lymph nodes in the axillary contents levels 1 and 2, the N stage is N1.

humanMachineDialogue.author: ZS Reasoning
humanMachineDialogue.text: The patient has metastatic carcinoma in one out of one sentinel lymph node (1/1) and metastatic carcinoma in four out of twenty four lymph nodes (4/24) in the right axillary contents, levels 1 and 2. This indicates that the cancer has spread to the lymph nodes, so the N stage is N1.
